  "title": "Electrical Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-     Handle project-works, eg. upgrading of switchboards and transformers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-     Conduct or arrange for site surveys, request quotation from contractors/ suppliers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-     Attend to meetings, site works and site discussions with clients, contractors and authorities on matters such as the scheduling of site activities.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-     Attend to call-out and emergency job request which include mobilization of contractor/supplier to site, urgent repairs, troubleshooting, restoration of power, site show-rounds and FSSB-testing.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-     Work with various parties, to be actively involved in project costing (cost breakdown and preparation of quotations), billings, claims, tender submissions etc.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-     Assist clients to prepare sample quotation form or technical specifications for servicing maintenance jobs and projects.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-     Negotiate pricing and liaise with contractors/suppliers for site activities.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-     Preparation of various operational reports and schedules</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-     Bachelor degree or equivalent from Electrical (Power) discipline with at least 1 year's relevant experience.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-     A team player, able to manage project, handle site work and irregular working hours.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>-     Possesses good communication skills</p>",
